<TITLE> 3 separate bodies to probe Joypurhat crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 18 (bdnews24.com) - Three separate committees have been formed to investigate Tuesday's truck-train collision in Joypurhat, said a ministry of information statement issued Wednesday. "A three member committee has been formed headed by Mohammad Shamsul Kibira, deputy secretary of the communication and railway division," said the statement. The committee will submit a report within five days, it added. Bangladesh Railway has also formed two separate probe bodies. A five-member committee was formed 'immediately' headed by Asim Talukdar, divisional signal and telecommunication engineer, and a four-member committee headed by Anhar Mahmud, chief engineer (west) has also been formed. Both will submit their reports within two days. The ministry quoted communications minister Syed Abul Hossain expressing deep anguish over those who died and hopes for the recovery of the injured. bdnews
